Fish diversity and abundance

This file summarizes fish data from sea grass monitoring transects. It was created Jan 2015 by ZLM for analysis of 2014 and 2015 monitoring data, but with the goal of be generalized to use for future years data as well.

Setup

Remove all objects for a clean start!

NOTE: this command will clear all your objects, dont run it if you have any unsaved objects you would like to keep.

NOTE2: this command should only be used when running this script directly; if you are sourcing multiple scripts including this one, make sure this is commented out, otherwise it will cause problems!

rm(list = ls())

Next, install packages that will be used for this script. Note that this command is currently commented out, if you do not have these packages, make sure you remove the hash and install them!

# install.packages(c("ggplot2", "dplyr", "magrittr))

Now the packages are install, make sure to load them

lapply(c("ggplot2", "dplyr", "magrittr"), library, character.only = T)

This script uses functions that are stored in a separate script, so well source that now.

source("fish.functions.R")

Formatting

Before getting to the data summary and figure making stages, well need to do some cleaning of formatting to make sure things are consistent with the other datasets. Here well also definite taxonomic subsets of the data to use later on.

Renaming and adding factors

The variable Site_ID is currently formatted inconsistently, and both the region, and otter_dens variables are missing; well fix these using dplyr::mutate, and some ifelse statements.

fish <- fish %>%
  mutate(transect = Transect,
         Transect = Time_Start,
         site_id = as.factor(ifelse(Site_ID == "SC", "CS",
                                    ifelse(Site_ID == "LC", "CL",
                                           ifelse(Site_ID == "NT", "TN",
                                                  as.character(Site_ID))))),
         site    = ifelse(site_id == "CS", "Choked Sandspit",
                          ifelse(site_id == "CL", "Choked Lower",
                                 ifelse(site_id == "TB", "Triquet Bay",
                                        ifelse(site_id == "TN", "Triquet North",
                                               ifelse(site_id == "TB", "Triquet Bay",
                                                      ifelse(site_id == "GW", "Goose Southwest",
                                                             ifelse(site_id == "GE", "Goose Southeast",
                                                                    ifelse(site_id == "MS", "McMullin South",
                                                                           ifelse(site_id == "MN", "McMullin North",
                                                                                  NA))))))))),
         region  = as.factor(ifelse(site_id == "CS" | site_id == "CL", "Choked",
                                   ifelse(site_id == "TB" | site_id == "TN", "Triquet",
                                          ifelse(site_id == "GE" | site_id == "GW", "Goose",
                                                 "McMullin")))),
         Common = ifelse(Common == "Black_rockfish", "black rockfish",
                         ifelse(Common == "Cabezon", "cabezon",
                                ifelse(Common == "Copper_rockfish", "copper rockfish",
                                       ifelse(Common == "Cresent_gunnel", "cresent gunnel",
                                              ifelse(Common == "Greenling", "unknown greenling",
                                                     ifelse(Common == "Gunnel", "unknown gunnel",
                                                            ifelse(Common == "Juvenile_Perch" | Common == "Perch", "unknown perch",
                                                                   ifelse(Common == "Juvenile_Rockfish", "unknown rockfish",
                                                                          ifelse(Common == "Kelp_Greenling", "kelp greenling",
                                                                                 ifelse(Common == "Kelp_perch", "kelp perch",
                                                                                        ifelse(Common == "Pacific_herring", "pacific herring",
                                                                                               ifelse(Common == "Quillback", "quillback rockfish",
                                                                                                      ifelse(Common == "Red_Irish_Lord", "red irish lord",
                                                                                                             ifelse(Common == "Sanddab", "unknown sanddab",
                                                                                                                    ifelse(Common == "Sandlance", "sandlance",
                                                                                                                           ifelse(Common == "Sculpin", "unknown sculpin",
                                                                                                                                  ifelse(Common == "Shiner_perch", "shiner perch",
                                                                                                                                         ifelse(Common == "Starry_Flounder", "starry flounder",
                                                                                                                                                ifelse(Common == "Striped_perch", "striped perch",
                                                                                                                                                       ifelse(Common == "Tubesnout", "tubesnout",
                                                                                                                                                              ifelse(Common == "Whitespotted_greenling", "white-spotted greenling",
                                                                                                                                                                     NA)))))))))))))))))))))) %>%
  subset(Mode %in% "SCUBA")  # select only SCUBA surveys

Adding absences

This section is for adding in absence data. Currently, survey data only record species that are observed, while unobserved species are implicitly absent. However, in order for average fish (or fish species) per transect to not be conditional on presence, the absences must be explicit. The following code chunk below checks each transect for each fish species, and when they are absent, adds an entry with a zero count.

# Create fish species, and site variables first
fish.spp <- subset(unique(fish$Common), !grepl("unknown", unique(fish$Common)))
fish.sites <- unique(fish$site)
fish$unique.tran <- as.factor(with(fish, paste(site, Transect, Diver, sep = "::")))
unique.tran <- unique(fish$unique.tran)

# for each site...
for (i in 1:length(unique.tran)) {
  tmp.fish.tran <-
    subset(fish, unique.tran %in% unique.tran[i]) 
      
  tmp.metadata <- 
    tmp.fish.tran %>%
    group_by(Date, Site, Site_ID, Diver, Mode, Transect, Depth_m, Time_Start,
             site_id, site, region, transect, unique.tran) %>%
    # group_by(year, day, region, site, site_id, Transect, survey, diver, mode,
    #          tran_length, tran_type, time_start, time_end, tide_start,
    #          tide_end, vis_ft, current_cat, depth_m, unique.tran) %>%
    summarise() 
      
  tmp.metadata$Common    <- NA
  tmp.metadata$Species   <- NA
  tmp.metadata$Length_cm <- NA
  tmp.metadata$Estimate  <- 0
  tmp.metadata$Notes     <- "implicit zero"

  # for each fish species...
  for (j in 1:length(fish.spp)) {
    # if fish species j does not show up in any row, add new row
    if (length(grep(fish.spp[j], tmp.fish.tran$Common)) == 0) {
      tmp.metadata$Common <- fish.spp[j]
      fish <- rbind(fish, tmp.metadata)
      } else { # if fish species j is present, move on
        next
    }
  }
}

Defining taxonomic subsets

Here well subset the fish dataset into a couple smaller groups of interest, rockfish and flatfish, for a more indepth look.

fish.noschool  <- subset(fish, !grepl("herring|lance|perch|tubesnout", fish$Common))

fish.rock      <- subset(fish, grepl("rockfish", fish$Common))

fish.flat      <- subset(fish, grepl("sanddab|flounder|sole", fish$Common))

fish.schooling <- subset(fish, grepl("herring|lance|perch|tubesnout", fish$Common))

Summaries

This section will calculate abundance, richness, and diversity (using H`, the Shannon Index), by site, and by region. This is done first for all fish, then for the two taxonomic subsets we specified earlier: rockfish, and flat fish. Figures of the same summary data will follow directyl after.
